Can you hear my heartbeat
Baby I trust you my friend
Are you seriously going on hiatus?
Mashiro is drawing with no intention of going on hiatus.
You saw him in the hospital, did not you?
Mashiro probably will not be happy if all of you go on hiatus for TRAP's sake.
Yeah, probably not.
He might blame himself.
That is why we should not tell him about this.
Anyway, if the Chief Editor does not go back on his decision about putting TRAP on hiatus,
we will also put our four manga on hiatus.
That is what we have decided!
How long will this hiatus last?
Until Jack prints TRAP again, of course!
No objections.
How will you be able to keep your assistants until that happens?
You will not be able to continue paying them, right?
T-That is true...
I do not have enough to keep paying them until April.
I will take care of that.
I have got tons of money and nothing to spend it on.
I am glad it can come in handy.
That is what happens when someone sells 8.5 million copies over ten volumes.
How much do you want him to back down?
I am also dissatisfied with a hiatus until April.
If the Chief Editor said that the hiatus will only last until Mashiro gets out of the hospital, would you resume drawing?
Whether it is April or until he is discharged, we will not draw until TRAP appears in Jack again.
Hiramaru, you are just being an opportunist here.
Shut up.
W-What?!
We have all united together because we resent the steps the Chief Editor's taken.
It is not that I do not want to draw manga...
Liar.
Well, how about it?
I will not go for that.
If you are going to lay out conditions, persuade the Chief Editor first.
Looks like they are committed to this.
So, if the hiatus looks like it will last for many months, we will simply move to another magazine.
Should we say that yet?
D-Do not be ridiculous!
We will all be fired!
Is that so?
Well, Yuujirou's been doing a good job for me...
Then I will just keep going and let my manga pile up.
I want to keep drawing, you see.
Please do so.
Nakai, Aoki, do you get it?
For hideout, going on hiatus will not work the same way as it does for a popular manga such as CROW.
You might be discontinued if you take this chance.
T-That will be bad...
I do not mind.
I would rather willingly cancel our manga than deal with a Chief Editor who makes such unjust decisions.
I believe that he is wrong.
Yeah!
Miss Aoki is the best!
Bravo!
Bravo!
I like you, Aoki.
I am telling you...!
There is no point in talking here with just the editors.
We will go to the Chief Editor and let him have it.
Yes!
Let us tell him clearly that we are taking a break.
Hey, wait!
We will talk this over with the Chief Editor,
but you guys should not come along.
Why?
It will get complicated.
Like that huge mess with KOOGY.
Why cannot they come with us?
I do not agree with the Chief Editor on this one, either.
Also, I have a hard time imagining these two quitting their boycott anytime soon.
Of course not!
Yuujirou is a reasonable man.
Even so, you would better continue drawing your manuscripts.
The Chief Editor may take back his decisions about TRAP at any time.
Roger!
I know.
Wha...?
Hiramaru, you also need to keep drawing.
Got it?
W-Well, of course!
How could you think I would not, Mr. Yoshida?
Chief, may we have a word with you?
What is so important that my two lead editors need to speak with me?
Niizuma Eiji, Hiramaru Kazuya, Fukuda Shinta, and the team of Aoki Kou and Nakai Takuro...
in protest against your decision, have declared that they will also go on hiatus for the duration of the time that TRAP is on hiatus.
In other words, this is a boycott?
Yes.
Of course, we will keep trying to convince them.
However, they are resolved in their decision.
At this point, they definitely will go on hiatus.
If the manuscripts fail to make their deadlines, that is the responsibility of the supervising editor,
and therefore, it becomes my responsibility as Chief Editor.
Well, again, if you remove the hiatus on TRAP, the four manga will resume
TRAP's hiatus is a settled matter.
Put forth your best efforts to see that those four manga's manuscripts continue to come in.
That is all I have to say.
But Chief...
This is something I have already decided.
Chief!
Do not worry, Mom.
I know my own body best.
You never listen to me!
Good afternoon!
Miura!
Hi!
How are you feeling?
The Chief Editor said he will not print TRAP even if I keep drawing,
but I will not give up until the very end.
I will finish it by Friday like always!
If the manuscript gets finished, I will come and pick it up.
After his surgery, if he properly finishes his manuscripts,
the Chief Editor might re-think his decision and resume printing earlier than he said he would!
Y-Yeah.
Will not you at least make the hiatus only until Mashiro gets better...
instead of until Ashirogi Muto graduate from high school?
If you do that, then it may be possible to convince Niizuma and the others
Do not make me repeat myself.
What are you doing?
Make sure your authors do not let their manuscripts fall behind.
Shujin.
Sorry, but can you come by early tomorrow to take the manuscript to our office?
Mashiro, take it easy...
I know.
I am sorry, madam.
I should be trying to stop him...
No.
I know full well that he will not stop.
He is stubborn, just like his father.
I should not tell him about the boycott.
He will just blame himself.
Come in.
Hello.
Miho!
Then I will come by on Friday to get the manuscript.
Yes, please do.
I will go home, then.
I have to make dinner for your grandpa.
Well, let us go, Miyoshi.
Oh, right.
You can stay, Kaya.
Takagi, too.
What are you saying?
We will let you have some time alone together.
Kiss him!
Kiss!
See ya!
Oh, Kaya...
My surgery's been scheduled for this coming Monday.
I see.
Mashiro.
Here.
I am worried about your surgery, after all.
Thanks.
On the day of your surgery, I will skip school and come here.
You do not have to do that.
It is a surgery with a 99 rate of success.
Huh?
What about the 1?
I am definitely coming.
It will be okay, right?
Yeah.
We are high school seniors, are not we?
Yeah.
Um, why are you saying something so obvious?
Kaya just said...
Kiss him!
Kiss!
C-Could she...!?
A-Azuki, because I have a 1 chance of dying, are you going to...?
Huh?
What are you saying?
I do not think you will die.
Why did you say that?
S-Sorry!
I mean that I could die without having kissed
That is not it.
I wonder if I am being strange.
I do not think I want to kiss you.
Oh, not like that.
I have never felt like I have wanted to.
I think I understand.
Really?
When I am with you, it is like the inside of my head goes blank,
so I am not thinking about that at all.
It is like, I am just happy that we are together.
I am glad.
I feel that way, too.
Is that really for the best?
I feel like I am not treating you right.
It is fine.
I am leaving him in your care, Doctor.
He will be fine, madam.
Please do not worry so much.
Yes.
Do not make that face, Miyoshi.
I am the one who should be nervous.
Yeah...
Would friends and family please wait in another room?
Oh, yeah.
Well, I am going in.
Good luck, Mashiro.
Even you are worried.
I will be fine.
I have your good luck charm.
Roll him in.
Okay.
I am glad your surgery went well.
Yes, I can leave the hospital soon.
Do not push yourself.
I have a present for you two today.
The first volume of Detective TRAP!
It just got delivered today.
A-Awesome!
It is like a real manga!
It is a real manga!
This will be lined up in stores all over the country, right?
Of course!
Are not you Mr. Obvious today.
It is no good.
I cannot read it with tears in my eyes.
Saiko, let us hurry up and resume serialization!
Yeah!
You are just being stubborn about handing it over.
Are you okay with betraying your readers like that?!
I apologize, but it is already settled.
Hail boycotting!
So you will not change your mind, then.
Of course not.
So you would better change the Chief Editor's mind.
I truly apologize.
Please wait a bit.
Chief.
What?
The printing office will not wait any longer.
I know it is not in there, but I will not believe it until I see it.
Yeah.
It is kind of lonely.
Hm?
Huh?
What?
It is not just TRAP!
CROW, KIYOSHI, Otters, and hideout door are not in here, either!
W-Why?!
Miura, what exactly does this mean?!
Since TRAP has been forced to go on hiatus, they are also boycotting.
The reason put here for us is Due to sudden illness,
but the reason put for them is Due to circumstances of the author.
Is not it going to be a big problem if Jack gets published like this?
Oh, all you authors are awesome!
Cannot wait to see what happens on Monday.
Really awesome!
In any case, we have taken a break for one week.
I will use that time to draw an even better manuscript.
Well, now I can rest for a week.
You are the one who seems to be the happiest about the hiatus, Hiramaru.
Fukuda and the rest have said that they will go on hiatus until TRAP is printed in Jack again.
That is what they are demanding.
I will not have that!
It is not right for everyone to have to take a break for our sake!
Right!
Mashiro, if you get too excited, your stitches will...
Most importantly, the readers...
What about the readers who look forward to those manga every week?!
I understand how you feel.
Will you accept a hiatus until you are discharged?
W-Why are even you talking about that?
Chapters 20 and 21 are ready!
I will even have chapter 22 done by Monday!
I know, but...
If we can convince the Chief Editor with that condition,
Fukuda and the rest may stop boycotting,
because they are the most upset about you having to go on hiatus until you graduate.
I do not want them to have to take a break.
If that is the only way...
I am very sorry.
In regard to that matter,
as explained in the publication it is due to authors' circumstances...
This is Jack's Editing Department.
I am sorry.
Regarding your inquiry of the hiatus this week...
Well, of course this would happen.
Jack has five titles on hiatus.
It would even make the news.
Akira!
Yuujirou!
Why are you just sitting there and chatting?!
Answer the phones!
The phones were off the hook this morning.
Things calmed down a bit in the afternoon.
I see.
If this mass hiatus continues next week, it will be an even bigger problem.
You may not be able to accept it, but...
Miura.
Can you call Fukuda and Niizuma here?
Do not give me that shit!
If they have finished, then just knock them down and grab the manuscripts!
That is an old-fashioned way of thinking.
Listen up!
If next week's issue still has those four manga on hiatus,
prepare to be fired!
It is not just you.
The Chief Editor's head may roll for this!
Well, it is not like we can just...
I will try to obtain it.
Miura's calling me, so I am heading out for a bit.
Are not I more important than Miura?
Yes, in terms of office hierarchy.
Please stop your boycott.
We are fine with a hiatus until I am discharged.
Are you really fine with that?
We do not have a choice.
I do not want to, but it is my fault for getting sick.
Ashirogi themselves are saying it.
You should end this.
Wait a minute.
Do we have your guarantee that if we stop the boycott,
TRAP will resume as soon as he gets discharged from the hospital?
Er, not yet.
What is with that?
If Ashirogi is okay with that, then I am, too.
Really?
Then I will put my neck on the line to convince the Chief Editor.
I did not agree with him on this in the first place.
I do not really care about your neck, though.
All right!
Fine!
But if TRAP is not resumed after all this, I will really lose it and wring your neck myself!
Y-Yeah!
That is how it is, Hiramaru.
I-I am so glad.
The readers are waiting for Otters...
Good job on convincing them.
However, TRAP will only resume after Ashirogi Muto graduate from high school.
Chief!
Yuujirou, do not get so fired up!
We still have time...
It is not something that will be resolved with more time!
I will send CROW and KIYOSHI to the press.
What should I do?
I want to get their serialization resumed as quickly as possible.
They really are serious.
What can I do for them as their editor?
It got announced, huh?
Yeah, but that was planned over six months ago.
And our second volume has been postponed until after we resume.
He got ahead of us again.
Has the Chief Editor still not agreed yet?
N-No...
That is not fair, since they already agreed to stop the boycott.
I am sorry.
Chapter 25 is finished.
A-All right.
I will look at it right now.
Amazing.
The quality has not dropped at all since he is been in the hospital.
On the contrary, it is improved!
TRAP is really good.
Even so...
But you know,
at this rate, they will have stopped boycotting for no reason!
Which means that if it is not resumed once he gets out, then Fukuda really will go crazy.
He is kept up with his manuscripts, though.
Mashiro's working hard.
By September, we will have about 10 unpublished chapters.
No matter how many we will have, all we can do now is make manga.
That is it!
I do not know if it will work, but it is definitely worth trying!
We do not talk much, do we?
If our dreams come true and we g-get married...
it might still be like this.
Probably.
Probably?
Even if we stop being so shy, we are just normally quiet people.
Does that sound okay to you?
Yeah, it is fine.
I think so, too.
What is most important now is to keep working hard, without giving up.
Congrats on your discharge!
Sorry for worrying you.
Then, let us go.
Yes!
Finally, huh?
Sorry, Mom.
I will be heading to the editorial department before going home...
Oh, it is fine.
I understand.
Go on.
Then, I will be going.
Yeah.
I am also dissatisfied with a hiatus until April.
It is not something that will be resolved with more time!
An editor's job is to receive the manuscript from the authors...
and to make sure it is put on the page.
These are the manuscripts he drew while in the hospital.
One per week.
He handed them in one by one without a drop in quality.
On the contrary, they got even better!
I have 11 chapters here.
Which means that if you start publishing them now,
they will last until the end of the year!
Mashiro has also made a complete recovery.
More than anything, the fact that he drew all of these while in the hospital...
proves his strength to continue serializing!
While you set all this up, did you stop to think about what you would have done in the worst case scenario?
I refused to let anyone stop me!
I also went along with it!
M-My uncle, Kawaguchi Tarou, said that until you get serialized, it is about conceit, effort, and luck.
Once you have managed to get serialized, it is physical strength, emotional strength, and finally, guts!
Kawaguchi Tarou read too many sports manga.
Fine.
I will gladly accept your gutsy manuscripts.
I will resume TRAP as quickly as possible!
Thank you!
Thank god...
We did it!
Those three really did it.
Guts, of all things...
Is this the 80's, or something?
Miura.
Th-This is the same thing you did before the serialization meeting...
Takagi, Mashiro.
Yes?
You pushed it way too far!
S-Sorry.
You did well.
You tried really hard!
I can finally draw manga again!
Aoki and I will not lose, either!
But being a pro is really tough.
Resumption and Low-Rank.
I had a dream about going on a date with Aoki!
